          "reviewBody": "Schools seems good, but staff has to understand etiquette.\n1. At first you visit to school they are ready with rate card (not about syllabus , not about pattern )\n2. First they have to show school\nEnvironment, classrooms and students growth plan\n3. With rate card minimum information available and few hidden charges like transpiration , uniform will be released once admission confirms\n4. Not enough play ground area\n5.  Expect change instead of business perspective student and education perspective",
